ANTHRAX, BOVINE - AZERBAIJAN: SUSPECTED
***************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Sponsored in part by Elsevier, publisher of
Journal of Clinical Virology
<http://intl.elsevierhealth.com/journals/jocv>
Date: Fri 2 Sep 2005
From: Natalia Pshenichnaya <crane@aaanet.ru>
Source: News agency Regnum, 2 Sep 2005 [translated by Mod.NP, edited]
<http://www.regnum.ru/news/506705.html>

The news agency Azepi-Press reports that anthrax has been registered in the
villages of Uzunoba, Nazarabad, and Didivar of the Babeksky district in the
Nakhychevanskaya Autonomous Republic of Azerbaijan.
According to the inhabitants of these villages, deaths of cattle due to
anthrax have occurred there. Local residents have buried the dead cattle.
According to the inhabitants of Uzunoba village, they threw the carcass of
one animal out of the village. On that day, unknown persons cut up the
carcass and took the meat of the dead animal. Measures for prevention of
spread of the illness are being undertaken.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[It was not possible to find any other additional information about this
case. - Mod.NP
If anyone has more definite information about what is going on, it would be
appreciated if that information could be shared with ProMED-mail. There
appears to be a widespread problem with disease and proper supervision of
carcass disposal. - Mod.MHJ]
